---
import EtsySoon from "../components/EtsySoon.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Hog Splitter Pro | Precision stopwatch for curling"
  description="Hog Splitter Pro is a revolutionary stopwatch for curlers: stateless splits, paired back-to-hog and hog-to-hog history, e-paper display, and USB-C charging."
  ogImage="/images/prototype.jpg"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-brand">
        <p class="hero-brand__tagline">The ultimate curling stopwatch</p>
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-tagline">Never miss another split</h1>
      <div class="marketing-copy">
        <p>
          Hog Splitter Pro is a revolutionary stopwatch crafted specifically for curlers. My mission was to create a tool
          that meets the unique timing needs of the sport with simplicity and efficiency.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Capture <strong>back-to-hog</strong> and <strong>hog-to-hog</strong> times for the same shot.</li>
          <li>Stateless design – <strong>no resets</strong> or confusing modes, and no annoying alarms.</li>
          <li><strong>Glanceable history</strong> of times – no scrolling or cycling required.</li>
          <li><strong>Large, high contrast display</strong> – visible at any angle.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Unlike other stopwatches on the market, Hog Splitter Pro combines all these features into one elegant device.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <EtsySoon variant="button" />
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/guide/">Read the product guide</a>
      </div>
      <p class="order-availability">Available for order in June 2026</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-screen-aside">
      <img
        class="hero-product-photo"
        src="/images/prototype.jpg"
        alt="Hog Splitter Pro handheld timer with e-paper display in its 3D-printed housing"
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="marketing-copy">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Each time you press the Split button, the main time readout shows the amount of time that elapsed between the
          last 2 button presses.
        </li>
        <li>Times are also shown in the history table - 6 rows of times are displayed by default.</li>
        <li>
          Any times less than 5.5 seconds are added to the left column, and times greater than 5.5 seconds are added to
          the right column.
        </li>
        <li>
          If a &quot;short time&quot; is immediately followed by a &quot;long time&quot;, the two will be paired up on
          the same row. This allows the user to easily correlate the short time and long time for the same shot.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        The two top split buttons behave the same way—there are two for ergonomics, not for different modes. Press
        either one to register a split.
      </p>
      <p>
        For very long gaps between splits: intervals over 20 seconds are not added to scrollable history (the main
        readout still updates until the next rule applies). Over 59 seconds between splits, the large display shows a
        dashed placeholder; the exact pattern follows your main timer precision setting. Details are in the
        <a href="/guide/#timing">product guide</a>.
      </p>
      <p>There&apos;s no concept of a &quot;reset&quot;—just keep splitting!</p>
      <p>
        Hog Splitter Pro features a large e-paper display (the same technology found in most e-readers) that is highly
        visible from any angle. It comes with a USB-C rechargeable battery that lasts many hours on a single charge -
        enough to get you through a bonspiel.
      </p>
      <p>
        Hog Splitter Pro is customizable to meet your needs. You can customize the volume, pitch, and duration of the
        &quot;beep&quot; (or turn it off completely!) You can choose from 3 different font sizes for this history display.
        You can even change the level of precision on the display: tenths, hundredths, or thousandths.
      </p>

      <h2>Design and materials</h2>
      <p>
        Built using a programmable microcontroller with an e-ink display, Hog Splitter Pro is housed in a custom
        3D-printed ergonomic design.
      </p>

      <h2>Practical notes</h2>
      <p>
        As a device developed and iterated quickly for real ice use, there are a few areas worth being upfront about:
      </p>
      <h3>Battery life</h3>
      <p>
        It lasts several hours—often enough for an entire event—but needs to be charged periodically. For important
        sessions, start from a full charge shortly before you play.
      </p>
      <h3>Durability</h3>
      <p>
        Several early users have used their Hog Splitter Pro for an entire season with no issues. That said, extra care should be taken with a manually-assembled device. Furthermore, e-paper display may
        be sensitive to UV light or high temperatures (for example, leaving the unit in a hot car).
      </p>
      <h3>Display refresh</h3>
      <p>
        E-paper can leave faint ghosting between refreshes. Most curlers will not find it distracting for split timing,
        but it is something to be aware of.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <h3>How do you reset it?</h3>
      <p>
        You don&apos;t. Hog Splitter Pro is designed to be stateless with no interval reset in normal use—just keep
        splitting!
      </p>
      <h3>How long does it take to charge?</h3>
      <p>About 2–3 hours via USB-C.</p>
      <h3>How much does it cost?</h3>
      <p>
        Hog Splitter Pro is sold through the Hugs Curling Tech shop on <EtsySoon variant="inline" />. The base price is
        $70.00 USD, and customizations can be added for an additional fee.
      </p>

      <h2>Acknowledgements</h2>
      <p>
        A special thank you to Derek Corbett for his invaluable help with 3D CAD design and playtesting. I also extend my
        gratitude to Drew Tingen for brainstorming ideas and contributing to playtesting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="photos" aria-labelledby="photos-heading">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Product photos</p>
        <h2 id="photos-heading">Gallery</h2>
      </div>
      
    </div>
    <div class="photo-grid">
      <img
        src="/images/prototype.jpg"
        alt="Hog Splitter Pro handheld timer with e-paper display in its 3D-printed housing"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <div class="photo-stack">
        <img
          src="/images/hsp-off-with-clip-800.jpg"
          alt="Hog Splitter Pro powered off with belt clip visible"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/hsp-press-800.jpg"
          alt="Pressing a split button on Hog Splitter Pro"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="shop-heading">
    <div class="cta-band">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Hugs Curling Tech on Etsy</p>
        <h2 id="shop-heading">Shop Hog Splitter Pro</h2>
        <p>Order from the Hugs Curling Tech Etsy shop.</p>
      </div>
      <EtsySoon variant="button" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
    <div class="contact-card">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Get in touch</p>
        <h2 id="contact-heading">Contact</h2>
        <p class="contact-card__lede">
          Have questions about Hog Splitter Pro, your order, or want to collaborate? Reach out.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a class="contact-email" href="mailto:hogsplitter@tgau.me">hogsplitter@tgau.me</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
